annotationA: Syntaxin-5; Syntaxin 5 is a type II transmembrane protein in the Q-SNARE family that forms hetero tetramers required for membrane function in the early secretory pathway (ER and Golgi). It has been involved in cytokinesis during spermatogenesis
annotationB: Conserved oligomeric Golgi complex subunit 7; Required for normal Golgi function
